Now, when x is equal to 2-- so
for our proposed function,

00:02:12.040 --> 00:02:15.450
when you input a 2, it will
output a negative 2.

00:02:15.450 --> 00:02:16.960
Seems reasonable so far.

00:02:16.960 --> 00:02:19.590
You input a 3, it'll
output a 2.

00:02:19.590 --> 00:02:21.150
Still reasonable.

00:02:21.150 --> 00:02:25.540
Now, when x is equal to 4, if we
want this to be a function,

00:02:25.540 --> 00:02:31.095
what this graph is implying is
if you input x is equal to 4,

00:02:31.095 --> 00:02:33.840
that the value of the function,
or the proposed

00:02:33.840 --> 00:02:37.890
function, is both negative
1 and 5.

00:02:37.890 --> 00:02:43.660
So this is saying that if you
take 4 into our function, into

00:02:43.660 --> 00:02:46.440
our proposed function-- we
can't really call it a

00:02:46.440 --> 00:02:46.890
function yet.

00:02:46.890 --> 00:02:48.720
We're trying to see if we
can call it a function.

00:02:48.720 --> 00:02:52.930
So if you put into our proposed
function that it

00:02:52.930 --> 00:02:58.400
could get to negative 1 and/or
it could get to 5, this is

00:02:58.400 --> 00:02:59.230
